Aim
To trace the route to a remote host using traceroute and analyze the response time between routers.
Introduction
Traceroute is a network diagnostic tool used to identify the path taken by packets from the source system to a
destination host. It displays each hop (router) along the network path and measures the response time
between systems.
Traceroute helps network administrators analyze routing paths, troubleshoot connectivity issues, and
measure network delays.
Procedure
Step 1: Install traceroute
Open Kali Linux terminal and install traceroute:
sudo apt install traceroute -y
Step 2: Verify Installation
Check whether traceroute is installed:
traceroute --version
Step 3: Trace Route to Remote Host
Run the traceroute command:
traceroute google.com
Step 4: Analyze the Output
Observe:
• Number of hops
• Router IP addresses
• Response time between routers
Implementation
Command Used
traceroute google.com
Explanation
• traceroute → Network route tracing tool
• google.com → Target remote host
